  "texts": [
    "[44], Orvieto et al. [45] • Algorithmic stability: Chatterjee and Zielinski [46],Bousquet and Elisseeff [47] When deploying a model in real-world scenarios, encountering a distribution shift is almost inevitable.",
    "In practice, training data can only fully represent the actual distribution of inputs under the most straightforward circumstances.",
    "Thus, a more pertinent, albeit challenging, consideration is out-of-distribution generalization.",
    "As elucidated by Wolpert [48] in no free lunch theorems, without additional assumptions, all learning algorithms perform equally poorly.",
    "Even widely employed techniques such as cross-validation will lose to anti-cross-validation in half of the cases."
